	(text "The paper state that a low pass filter is required behind the DAC.\nUnfortunatly I don't understand half of what the paper require this filter to be D:\n(like I understand what caracterise a butterworth filter is but neither I\nknow how to make nor how to use it).\nSo I will make this board as is. Then do so testing to see what is \ngoing on, I mean, the specs says : \n\"capable of directly drive à 75 Ohm terminated cable\".\nI want/need to see the harmonics on my scope to get a better understanding."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 110.49 191.77 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "149c40a7-a23d-4872-ac16-26569a544a96")
	)
	(text "(pour 5V):\n56K -> 500mA (Le LDO est prévu pour ~1A (même si c'est overkill)).\n22k -> 1.5A	 (plus que suffisant !).\n10k -> 3A	 (Ultrakill).\n\nlien : https://www.beyondlogic.org/primer-usb-c-connector/"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 78.74 267.97 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left top)
		)
		(uuid "20376308-c6bb-4c54-8de4-f2de0e7d1008")
	)
